==English==

===Alternative forms===
* [[Achilles' tendon]]
* [[tendon of Achilles]]

===Etymology===
A [[calque]] of {{etyl|NL.|en}} {{term|Achillis tendo|lang=la}}, a term devised by the Dutch anatomist {{w|Philip Verheyden}} in 1693 in reference to the mythological account of [[Achilles]] being held by the heel when dipped in the {{w|Styx|River Styx}}.

===Noun===
{{en-noun|head=[[Achilles]] [[tendon]]}}

# {{context|anatomy|lang=en}} The strong [[tendon]] formed of the united tendons of the large [[muscle]]s in the [[calf]] of the leg, and inserted into the bone of the heel.

====Synonyms====
* {{sense|anatomy}} [[calcaneal tendon]], [[tendo Achillis]], [[tendo calcaneus]]

